---
import "../../styles/global.css";
import Favicon from "../../components/ui/Favicon.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <Favicon />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="Forward Deployed Engineer at First Crack — embed with roasteries, ship solutions, close deals." />
    <title>Forward Deployed Engineer — First Crack Careers</title>
  </head>
  <body class="jd">
    <header class="jd-nav"><div class="jd-nav-inner"><a href="/" class="jd-nav-brand">First Crack</a><nav class="jd-nav-links"><a href="/careers" class="jd-nav-link jd-back">&larr; Back to jobs</a></nav></div></header>
    <main>
      <div class="jd-container">
        <div class="jd-layout">
          <article class="jd-main">
            <div class="jd-header">
              <span class="jd-dept">Engineering · Sales</span>
              <h1 class="jd-title">Forward Deployed Engineer</h1>
              <div class="jd-meta"><span class="jd-loc">Remote — APAC / EMEA</span><span class="jd-type">Full-time</span></div>
              <button type="button" class="jd-apply-btn" onclick="document.getElementById('apply-form').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})">Apply</button>
            </div>

            <section class="jd-section">
              <h2>About Us</h2>
              <p>First Crack builds desktop software that specialty coffee roasters rely on every day. Our application connects directly to roasting machines, displays live temperature curves, and manages everything from batch history to production scheduling. We're a small, remote-first team shipping on macOS and Windows with cloud sync for teams.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="jd-section">
              <h2>About the Role</h2>
              <p>You are the bridge between our product and our largest customers. As a Forward Deployed Engineer, you embed directly with roasteries — understanding their workflows, building custom integrations, and shipping solutions that make First Crack indispensable to their operation. You're part engineer, part consultant, part evangelist. You'll travel to roasteries, see the roast floor in action, and build the features that close deals.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="jd-section">
              <h2>Responsibilities</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Embed with enterprise roastery customers to understand their workflows and pain points</li>
                <li>Build custom integrations, scripts, and tooling to make First Crack fit their operation</li>
                <li>Work with the product team to translate customer needs into features and roadmap items</li>
                <li>Support the sales cycle with technical demos, proofs-of-concept, and on-site visits</li>
                <li>Create documentation, tutorials, and onboarding materials for large deployments</li>
                <li>Be the voice of the customer internally — advocate for the roast floor</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="jd-section">
              <h2>Desirable Skills, Knowledge, and Experience</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>3+ years in a technical role — engineering, solutions engineering, or technical consulting</li>
                <li>Comfortable writing code (Python, TypeScript, or similar) to solve customer problems</li>
                <li>Strong communication skills — you can talk to a roaster and a CTO in the same day</li>
                <li>Willingness to travel (20-40%) to roasteries across your region</li>
                <li>Experience with hardware integrations, IoT, or industrial software is a plus</li>
                <li>Genuine curiosity about specialty coffee — you'll be spending a lot of time on the roast floor</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="jd-section"><h2>Compensation</h2><p>Competitive salary based on experience and location, plus variable compensation tied to customer success. This role is eligible for equity participation.</p></section>

            <section class="jd-section">
              <h2>Benefits</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Remote-first — work from wherever your coffee tastes best</li>
                <li>Competitive pay &amp; meaningful equity</li>
                <li>Take-what-you-need vacation (we actually mean it)</li>
                <li>Tooling budget + AI credits stipend</li>
                <li>Coffee budget — green, roasted, brewing gear</li>
                <li>Hands-on roasting workshop for every new hire</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="jd-section jd-eeo"><p>First Crack is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to providing equal employment opportunity for all people and place great value in both diversity and inclusiveness. All qualified applicants will be considered for employment without regard to their, or any other person's, perceived or actual race, color, religion, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, physical or mental disability, medical condition, family care status, or any other basis protected by law.</p></section>
          </article>

          <aside class="jd-sidebar">
            <div class="jd-apply-card" id="apply-form">
              <h3>Apply for this job</h3>
              <p>Send your resume and tell us about a time you shipped something on-site with a customer.</p>
              <a href="mailto:careers@firstcrackiscoming.com?subject=Forward%20Deployed%20Engineer%20Application" class="jd-btn">Apply via email</a>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <footer class="jd-footer"><div class="jd-container"><span>First Crack &copy; 2026</span><nav><a href="/about">About</a><a href="/careers">Careers</a><a href="mailto:hello@firstcrackiscoming.com">Contact</a></nav></div></footer>
  </body>
</html>

<style is:global>
  :root { --jd-mint: #81fba5; --jd-dark: #0b0b0b; --jd-fg: #0b0b0b; --jd-fg-2: #4a4a4a; --jd-fg-muted: #767676; --jd-bg: #fff; --jd-border: rgba(0,0,0,0.08); --jd-border-s: rgba(0,0,0,0.14); --jd-sans: 'Pretendard Variable','Pretendard',system-ui,sans-serif; --jd-mono: 'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace; }
  .jd { margin: 0; font-family: var(--jd-sans); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--jd-fg); background: var(--jd-bg); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; }
  .jd *,.jd *::before,.jd *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .jd a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }
  .jd-container { max-width: 1100px; margin-inline: auto; padding-inline: 24px; }
  .jd-nav { position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 50; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.92); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--jd-border); }
  .jd-nav-inner { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; height: 56px; }
  .jd-nav-brand { font-family: var(--jd-sans); font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .jd-back { font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--jd-fg-2); transition: color 0.15s; }
  .jd-back:hover { color: var(--jd-fg); }
  .jd-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 48px; padding: 48px 0 80px; align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .jd-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; } }
  .jd-header { margin-bottom: 40px; padding-bottom: 32px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--jd-border); }
  .jd-dept { display: inline-block; font-family: var(--jd-mono); font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--jd-fg-muted); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .jd-title { font-family: var(--jd-sans); font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .jd-meta { display: flex; gap: 20px; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--jd-fg-muted); margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .jd-loc { color: var(--jd-mint); font-weight: 600; }
  .jd-apply-btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; height: 40px; padding: 0 24px; font-family: var(--jd-sans); font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600; border-radius: 0; background: var(--jd-dark); color: #fff; border: none; cursor: pointer; transition: opacity 0.15s; }
  .jd-apply-btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; }
  .jd-section { margin-bottom: 36px; }
  .jd-section h2 { font-family: var(--jd-sans); font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .jd-section p { font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--jd-fg-2); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .jd-section ul { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .jd-section li { position: relative; padding-left: 18px; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--jd-fg-2); }
  .jd-section li::before { content: ""; position: absolute; left: 3px; top: 0.65em; width: 4px; height: 4px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--jd-mint); }
  .jd-eeo { padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--jd-border); }
  .jd-eeo p { font-size: 0.8125rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--jd-fg-muted); }
  .jd-apply-card { position: sticky; top: 80px; padding: 28px; border: 1px solid var(--jd-border); border-radius: 0; background: var(--jd-bg); }
  .jd-apply-card h3 { font-family: var(--jd-sans); font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .jd-apply-card p { font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--jd-fg-2); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .jd-btn { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; height: 44px; width: 100%; font-family: var(--jd-sans); font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600; border-radius: 0; background: var(--jd-mint); color: var(--jd-dark); text-decoration: none; transition: opacity 0.15s; }
  .jd-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }
  .jd-apply-note { font-family: var(--jd-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--jd-fg-muted); text-align: center; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 0; }
  .jd-footer { background: var(--jd-dark); padding: 24px 0; }
  .jd-footer .jd-container { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; }
  .jd-footer span { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); }
  .jd-footer nav { display: flex; gap: 20px; }
  .jd-footer nav a { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s; }
  .jd-footer nav a:hover { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); }
  @media (max-width: 639px) { .jd-footer .jd-container { flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; } }
</style>
